[4] Indonesia (Jakarta, W. Sumatra) - 70th and 71st death
Date: Thu 29 Mar 2007
From: Mary Marshall <tropical.forestry@btinternet.com>
Source: Reuters Foundation AlertNet [edited]
<http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/JAK134695.htm>

Indonesia: 2 more bird flu deaths
-----------------------------------
A 14-year-old boy and a 28-year-old woman have died of bird flu in
Indonesia, a health ministry official said on Thursday [29 Mar 2007].
The deaths brought Indonesia's confirmed human death toll from the
H5N1 virus to 71, the highest in the world.
The boy was from West Sumatra and died on 24 Mar 2007, while the
woman was from the capital, Jakarta, and died on Wednesday [28 Mar
2007], Joko Suyono of the Ministry's bird flu centre said by telephone.
--
